						<h2>
						Background and Objectives
						</h2>
					</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td style="text-align:justify; font-size:18px">
<p>
Water is vital for life, pivotal for human development and necessary to keep our environment healthy. It is a fundamental resource necessary for human well-being and ecosystem functioning. There is a fixed amount of water on the planet and with increasing population, economic development and changing lifestyles that has imposed considerable pressure on the worldâ€™s limited water resources leading to increased competition for water and creating situations of potential conflict. Thus the sustainable management of water is a key issue in future societal development.
</p>	
<p>
The concept of Water Resource Management (WRM) has gained wide acceptance as a successful way to tackle these challenges. The aim is to promote economic and social development by addressing and balancing diverse water use interests, while simultaneously safeguarding water resources. However, current water management practices are
far from fulfilling these objectives for different reasons. In some cases,adequate management structures and techniques are not available while in other cases existing management approaches fail in properly addressing the key problems.
</p>
<p>
The conference focuses in providing an opportunity for academicians, researchers, scientists, practitioners, water managers and professionals from economy, administration, international agencies, private institutions and consulting establishments to come together to express their opinions and interests...
<a href="index.php?page=detailed-objective">
